canonical:
  title: 三辭不允批答
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 一國安危所係者重大臣去就未可以輕何勵節於戒盈欲全身而求退卿山川閒氣日月孤忠仗義廻軍則家國再寧正名定策則神人咸喜及玆新造之隙賴卿篤棐之材方將共政以致平豈可托辭而規免謗興則可以理遣病革則當用毉治不必釋位以閒居乃能怡神而善保旣煩三讓惟兾小安
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 三辭不允批答
  author: 李詹
  language: lzh
  text: 一國安危。所係者重。大臣去就。未可以輕。何勵節於戒盈。欲全身而求退。卿山川閒氣。日月孤忠。仗義廻軍則家國再寧。正名定策則神人咸喜。及玆新造之隙。賴卿篤棐之材。方將共政以致平。豈可托辭而規免。謗興則可以理遣。病革則當用毉治。不必釋位以閒居。乃能怡神而善保。旣煩三讓。惟兾小安。
korean:
  title: 삼사 불윤 비답
  author: 이첨
  language: kor
  text: 한 나라의 안위는 관계되는 바가 중하니, 대신의 거취는 가볍게 하지 못할 것인데, 어찌 가득 차는 것을 경계하려고만 하여 몸만 안전히 하려고 물러가기를 구하는가.경은 산천의 정기를 타고나 일월(日月) 같은 충성을 지녔다. 의(義)를 주장하여 군사를 돌이키매 국가가 다시 편안했고, 명분(名分)을 바로잡아 왕통을 결정하매 귀신과 사람이 모두 기뻐했다. 새로 국가를 만드는 비상시에 경의 힘써 돕는 재주를 힘입어 바야흐로 정사를 함께해 태평을 이룩하고자 하거늘, 어찌 핑계를 대면서 중임(重任)을 면하고자 하는가.비방이 일어난 것은 이치로써 참음이 옳고, 병이 중한 것은 약으로 다스림이 마땅할지니, 반드시 벼슬을 그만두고 한가히 있어야 마음에 기쁘고 양생에 좋은 것이 아니다. 이미 세 번이나 번거로이 사양했으니 그만 편하게 마음 먹기를 바라노라.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0330_010_0360&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Royal Response to Three Respectful Declines
  author: Lee Cham
  language: eng
  text: The fate of a nation rests upon shoulders of great weight. A minister's departure cannot be taken lightly. Why do you guard against excess only to seek refuge in safety, withdrawing from service? You were born from the essence of mountains and rivers, bearing loyalty bright as sun and moon. When you marshaled righteous force to turn the army back, our nation found peace again. When you rectified names and settled the succession, both spirits and men rejoiced. In this critical hour of our newly formed state, we depend upon your devoted talent and wisdom. We wish to govern together and bring forth harmony—how can you offer excuses to escape this sacred duty? Let slander be answered by reason and patience; let grave illness be treated by physicians. It is not by abandoning office to dwell idle that the spirit finds joy and life is well preserved. You have already declined three times with great courtesy. I ask only that you find peace in accepting.
  footnotes:
    - This is a royal response declining a minister's request for retirement. Lee Cham served as a trusted advisor during a period of political turmoil and succession.
    - The reference to 'righteous force' and 'rectifying names and settling succession' likely refers to Lee Cham's role in military and political stabilization during court upheaval.
    - The 'three times' mentioned refers to Lee Cham's repeated formal requests to step down from office.
